        "discriminators": [
          "UCS states the rule outright: 'a swish is smaller than a whoosh. Small objects make swishes.' Small object, less air moved: shorter, brighter, thinner.",
          "Versus SWOOSHES-WHOOSH: roughly a quarter the duration (~0.35 s vs ~1.5 s), roughly three times the spectral centroid (~3.5 kHz vs ~1.2 kHz), and a third the sub-200 Hz energy. A swish that is a second long with a chest-thumping low end is a whoosh.",
          "Versus DESIGNED-WHOOSH: same morphology, but designed whooshes are stylised -- heavier processing, more extreme centroid slope, often synthetic low end."
